				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">song nerf?<a name="75023"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 31 05 6:03 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok, I noticed something a few days ago while trying to go check to see if Vindi was up in Kael for a guild raid. I don't know if this was something nerfed a within a month or so and I just missed reading it somewhere, or some type bug. Basically, I used to be able to lull the giants that see invis and run to the arena with no problem. I noticed a few days ago that the lvl 66 lull lulled the mobs, but I was attacked when I ran by. Then I used my old lull, and same thing. I have used the old lull song countless times running through and never, ever had a problem. I was just wondering if they were nerfed and I missed reading it somewhere, or what is going on. I did find something from a past post on the new lull which may have contributed to me getting attacked, but doesnt make up for the old song, too.
<br />
This is from old post I found 
<br />

<br />
&quot;That is the way the song was designed. It is not a bug. 
<br />

<br />
Level 66 song Lucy description: 
<br />

<br />
1: Reaction Radius(10/70) 
<br />

<br />

<br />
Level 61 song Lucy description: 
<br />

<br />
1: Frenzy Radius(5/65) 
<br />
2: Reaction Radius(10/65) 
<br />
3: Pacify 
<br />

<br />

<br />
This change means that the &quot;assist&quot; range for social mobs is reduced with the 66 song, but the proximity agro range is unchanged, exactly as you describe. This was done deliberately in order to prevent us from skipping content with the new song&quot;
<br />

<br />

<br />
Any imput on this would be great. Thanks <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
